John Charles, Makurdi Benue State Governor, Samuel Ortom, on Thursday, presented a N132.5bn budget for the 2021 fiscal year to the State House of Assembly. The 2021 budget is N23.7bn higher than the 2020 revised budget of N108.8bn. While presenting the N132.5bn budget which he christened, ‘Budget of Resilience,’ Ortom said, of this  amount, N20bn would be spent on health and food security within the context of COVID-19. He also explained that the 2021 budget considered the need to strengthen the resilience of Benue people as well as the state as it seeks to recover from the economic crisis caused by the pandemic. A breakdown of the budget shows that the economic sector received the lion’s share with N51.3bn closely followed by the social sector with N44.5bn, while administration got N33.8bn. Copyright PUNCH.
